{"ts":"2026-06-27T03:18:27.146Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Component Relationships**\n\nI've determined that the components within `components/private-app` are exceptionally well-crafted, especially with their CSS, SVG, and custom theming. My next step involves identifying dependencies; I'm analyzing the `app/portal` and `app/admin` directories to understand which components utilize these high-quality elements. Following this, I will create a centralized mock data model file.\n\n\n**Verifying Type Re-Exports**\n\nI'm now investigating the potential to centralize type definitions. Initially, I reviewed `components/private-app/types.ts` and identified the existing types. I've decided to import the types defined in `/lib/mock-data-model.ts` into `components/private-app/types.ts` and re-export them. I believe this approach maintains a DRY codebase while keeping the type definitions centralized. Now, I'm verifying the feasibility of this strategy.\n\n\n**Resolving Naming Conflicts**\n\nI've just been reviewing `components/private-app/types.ts` again, and am now confident in moving forward. I've confirmed that there are no naming conflicts. I'm focusing on explicit imports to avoid clashes between types like `Notification` and `SystemNotification`, as well as `User` and `UserProfile`. There appear to be no immediate clashes with types like `ActivityEvent`, `Project`, and `AgentOperation`. I am moving forward with explicit imports.\n\n\n**Centralizing Type Definitions**\n\nI'm now confidently expanding the centralized type definitions. I've considered and avoided naming conflicts with types such as `GovernanceItem`, `Approval`, `ClientAccount`, `DocumentItem`, `Invoice`, `SupportTicket`, and `AnalyticsMetric`, since these are new and are absent in `components/private-app/types.ts`. Now, I'm defining these directly in that file. My architecture is to ensure that `components/private-app` is the source of truth for all of its types, and that `/lib/mock-data-model.ts` is the safe central location for all mock data.\n\n\n**Defining Mock Data Content**\n\nI'm now fully committed to the strategy of housing both types and mock data within `/lib/mock-data-model.ts`. This single file will serve as the source of truth, offering a self-contained and robust solution. The goal is to make this module fully deterministic and easy to use. I'm focusing on designing high-fidelity mock data and creating a narrative for a secure environment, with a visual metaphor of cryptographic keys and isolated boundaries.\n\n\n**Implementing Mock Data Model**\n\nI'm now implementing `/lib/mock-data-model.ts`, focusing on accuracy and clarity. I'm prioritizing descriptive field names like `sha256Hash` and labeling all data as `DEMO / PREVIEW DATA`. I've structured TypeScript interfaces and centralized datasets with matching IDs. Read-only data constants and getter functions will allow seamless consumption. This data model will be designed for easy pagination, and I'll avoid altering landing page or auth components.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T03:18:27.158Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"ss8u9ai7","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/lib/mock-data-model.ts","new_text":"/**\n * UI QUALITY CONSTITUTION - GFF AI PREVIEW DATA MODEL\n * \n * This file centralizes the complete, high-fidelity mock data model for the\n * Client Portal and Admin Portal as required by Task 77-phase4-private-mock-data-model.\n * \n * All data is deterministic, marked as demo/preview data, and contains no real-world clients or logos.\n */\n\n// ============================================================================\n// 1. DATA TYPES (15 REQUIRED TYPES)\n// ============================================================================\n\nexport interface ClientAccount {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  domain: string;\n  status: \"active\" | \"suspended\" | \"pending\";\n  tier: \"Sovereign\" | \"Enterprise\" | \"Standard\";\n  createdAt: string;\n  region: string;\n  complianceLevel: string;\n  contactName: string;\n  contactEmail: string;\n}\n\nexport interface Project {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  clientAccountId: string;\n  status: \"active\" | \"completed\" | \"paused\" | \"evaluating\";\n  desc: string;\n  enclaveType: \"Intel SGX\" | \"AMD SEV-SNP\" | \"AWS Nitro Enclave\";\n  nodesCount: number;\n  lastUpdated: string;\n  tag: string;\n}\n\nexport interface Program {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  status: \"active\" | \"completed\" | \"on_hold\";\n  progress: number; // percentage 0-100\n  projectIds: string[];\n}\n\nexport interface AgentOperation {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  projectId: string;\n  status: \"active\" | \"evaluating\" | \"decoupled\" | \"warning\";\n  threads: number;\n  memory: string;\n  logs: string[];\n  lastHeartbeat: string;\n}\n\nexport interface AgentHealth {\n  agentId: string;\n  status: \"healthy\" | \"warning\" | \"critical\" | \"offline\";\n  cpuUtilization: number; // 0-100\n  latencyMs: number;\n  memoryUtilization: number; // 0-100\n  uptimePercentage: number;\n}\n\nexport interface DocumentItem {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  size: string;\n  format: \"PDF\" | \"JSON\" | \"YAML\" | \"CSV\" | \"DOCX\";\n  hash: string; // SHA-256 preview\n  uploadedAt: string;\n  category: \"audit\" | \"governance\" | \"receipt\" | \"agreement\";\n  clearanceLevel: \"LEVEL_I\" | \"LEVEL_II\" | \"LEVEL_III\" | \"LEVEL_IV\" | \"LEVEL_V\";\n}\n\nexport interface Invoice {\n  id: string;\n  date: string;\n  amount: string;\n  status: \"paid\" | \"unpaid\" | \"processing\" | \"overdue\";\n  dueDate: string;\n  category: \"Compute Epoch\" | \"SLA Support\" | \"Telemetry Stream\" | \"Premium Support\";\n  hash: string; // SHA-256 cryptographic seal\n}\n\nexport interface SupportTicket {\n  id: string;\n  title: string;\n  status: \"open\" | \"resolved\" | \"in_progress\";\n  priority: \"high\" | \"medium\" | \"low\" | \"critical\";\n  createdAt: string;\n  desc: string;\n  replies: {\n    sender: string;\n    text: string;\n    timestamp: string;\n  }[];\n}\n\nexport interface AnalyticsMetric {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  value: string | number;\n  delta: string;\n  direction: \"up\" | \"down\" | \"neutral\";\n  status: \"normal\" | \"warning\" | \"stable\" | \"critical\";\n  sparkPoints: number[];\n}\n\nexport interface GovernanceItem {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  standard: \"ISO-27001\" | \"SOC2 Type II\" | \"HIPAA\" | \"GDPR Enclave\" | \"NIST AI RMF\";\n  status: \"compliant\" | \"non_compliant\" | \"warning\";\n  desc: string;\n  lastChecked: string;\n}\n\nexport interface Approval {\n  id: string;\n  title: string;\n  requester: string;\n  status: \"pending\" | \"approved\" | \"rejected\";\n  requestDate: string;\n  category: \"Enclave Provisioning\" | \"Model Boundary Shift\" | \"Access Elevation\" | \"HSM Seal Rollover\";\n}\n\nexport interface User {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  email: strin