{"ts":"2026-06-27T03:19:39.483Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing New Functionality**\n\nI'm now integrating new functionality related to previewing projects, programs, agent operations, and agent health metrics. Currently, the line count is at 303. I'm focusing on incorporating these new elements into the existing codebase, specifically the project-related components. The `previewProjects` function is the starting point, and I'll continue integrating the others.\n\n\n**Defining Project Parameters**\n\nI've been defining the parameters for several projects, focusing on data structure to represent project details effectively. I'm focusing on attributes like project IDs, names, client account IDs, statuses, descriptions, enclave types, node counts, last updated timestamps, and tags. This data structure will streamline how I handle and display project information within the system. This will impact the new functionality integration significantly.\n\n\n**Constructing Sample Data**\n\nI'm now building sample data for projects and programs. I've populated example `project` details including identifiers, names, statuses, descriptions, enclave types, node counts, update timestamps, and relevant tags. I've also incorporated sample data for `programs` that contain program IDs, names, statuses, progress indicators, and linked project IDs. Next, I'll work on similar sample data for agent operations.\n\n\n**Incorporating Agent Data**\n\nI'm now integrating agent data to provide real-time agent operations monitoring. I'm focusing on attributes like IDs, names, project affiliations, statuses, threads, memory usage, logs, and last heartbeats. This data will be critical for the agent health metrics, and will influence how I present this to the user. I plan to refine the data display to enhance the agent management interface.\n\n\n**Evaluating Agent Health Metrics**\n\nI'm now diving into the agent health metrics, d